{
  "text": "The electrophoretic mobilities of the first complexes formed with 6mG-containing dsDNAs are greater than those of the saturated complexes. This suggests that they might contain fewer molecules of protein than are present in the saturated complexes [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . To test this, we measured the stoichiometric differences between free dsDNA and the first binding state and between the first and second binding states. Species concentrations were calculated from EMSA band intensities and the dependence of ln (",
  "correct_citation": {
